WEBVTT

00:02.414 --> 00:04.833
Courtney: ♪ My city love me, never
catch me on the wrong street ♪

00:04.834 --> 00:06.953
♪ Hustle all I do,
but do it to a strong beat ♪

00:06.954 --> 00:09.533
♪ Yeah, I'm Courtney Rose,
and I grew up out the concrete ♪

00:09.534 --> 00:11.333
♪ But come and see me
where I live, man ♪

00:11.334 --> 00:13.333
♪ But come and see me
where I live, man ♪

00:13.334 --> 00:15.034
- ♪ Come and see me where I live, man ♪
- [Cellphone ringing]

00:15.035 --> 00:16.848
♪ But come and see me
where I live, man ♪

00:16.873 --> 00:19.333
I be right here. Right here.

00:19.334 --> 00:21.031
♪ Come and see me where I live, man ♪

00:21.085 --> 00:22.874
♪ But come and see me
where I live, man ♪

00:22.875 --> 00:24.251
- <i>I'm Beverly Michaels...</i>
- ♪ Come and see me, I'll be right here ♪

00:24.305 --> 00:26.714
<i>...reporting live here at the
intersection of First and Main,</i>

00:26.715 --> 00:28.505
- <i>where you can see right behind me...</i>
- There she is!

00:28.508 --> 00:30.714
I missed you, gorgeous!

00:30.715 --> 00:32.794
Where your fine twin sister at?

00:32.795 --> 00:35.914
Damn! How you doin', shorty?
What, what?

00:35.915 --> 00:37.874
I can't control who says hi to me.

00:37.875 --> 00:39.294
Yeah, maybe you did need a dad
after all.

00:39.295 --> 00:41.044
[Chuckles] What's up, Ma? How was work?

00:41.045 --> 00:42.515
Oh, no, I can't even talk about it.

00:42.540 --> 00:44.674
Nope. I can't do it. Not today.

00:44.675 --> 00:46.875
- You know my manicurist, Roberta?
- Is it weird that I do?

00:46.878 --> 00:49.215
- And you know my gas station guy, Maurice?
- Yeah, it's weird.

00:49.218 --> 00:50.964
Well, guess what they have in common.

00:50.965 --> 00:52.754
A secret baby!

00:52.755 --> 00:53.795
You know how I found out?

00:53.796 --> 00:54.834
You read his mail.

00:54.835 --> 00:56.624
No! I read her mail.

00:56.625 --> 00:58.215
- Oh! Check it out. It's on.
- [Theme music plays]

00:58.218 --> 00:59.414
All right.

00:59.415 --> 01:01.511
<i>Channel 8's Gabby Montoya reports.</i>

01:01.536 --> 01:03.464
Gabby: <i>If you haven't heard
the name Courtney Rose,</i>

01:03.465 --> 01:04.623
<i>you're not alone.</i>

01:04.625 --> 01:06.294
Wasn't she in "Bachelor in Paradise?"

01:06.295 --> 01:07.914
♪ Grow old, Netflix and chill... ♪

01:07.915 --> 01:10.414
Gabby: <i>He's a 27-year-old
struggling rapper</i>

01:10.415 --> 01:13.044
<i>who performs at small shows
in Northern California.</i>

01:13.045 --> 01:15.414
<i>Now he's adding a new title
to his playlist...</i>

01:15.415 --> 01:16.874
<i>candidate for mayor.</i>

01:16.875 --> 01:18.643
So, yeah, it turns out it's super easy

01:18.668 --> 01:19.888
to run for local office.

01:19.913 --> 01:22.334
Step one, get 200 signatures.
Step two, don't be a felon.

01:22.335 --> 01:24.674
And I don't go to trial till next year.

01:24.675 --> 01:26.254
I'm just playing, Ma. I love you.

01:26.255 --> 01:28.464
<i>But organizing a campaign takes help.</i>

01:28.465 --> 01:30.544
<i>Enter Rose's two best friends
from high school.</i>

01:30.545 --> 01:32.914
So... So we couldn't have done
it without our generous donors.

01:32.915 --> 01:35.674
Mastercard, Discover, Visa.

01:35.675 --> 01:37.625
- Yeeza.
- What?

01:37.628 --> 01:39.504
It's Yeez... Yeezy's Visa.

01:39.505 --> 01:40.915
- Oh. [Laughs] Oh!
- [Cellphone rings]

01:40.918 --> 01:42.375
- Mm-hmm.
- Hello. [Clears throat]

01:42.376 --> 01:43.964
You've reached Courtney Rose for Mayor

01:43.965 --> 01:45.874
and/or T.K.'s personal cellphone.

01:45.875 --> 01:47.754
How may I direct your call?

01:47.755 --> 01:50.374
<i>One woman not voting
for Rose... his old classmate</i>

01:50.375 --> 01:52.544
<i>and rival campaign manager,
Valentina Barella.</i>

01:52.545 --> 01:54.714
Courtney Rose
is a know-nothing egomaniac

01:54.715 --> 01:56.464
whose entire campaign is a stunt.

01:56.465 --> 01:59.174
Voters won't fall for that.
Not in America.

01:59.175 --> 02:00.874
Is Courtney Rose for real,

02:00.875 --> 02:03.038
or is he just an election sideshow?

02:03.076 --> 02:05.138
- <i>Either way, this local rapper</i>
- In the name of Jehovah,

02:05.162 --> 02:06.757
- <i>will have to beat...</i>
- why are you doing this?

02:06.758 --> 02:08.161
- <i>...the competition.</i>
- Why does anyone in my generation

02:08.186 --> 02:10.125
- <i>Gabby Montoya, Channel 8 News.</i>
- do anything? Attention.

02:10.127 --> 02:11.674
Ma, okay. H-Hear me out.

02:11.675 --> 02:13.044
I know I'm a good rapper.

02:13.045 --> 02:14.714
Nothing that spent nine months
in me is good.

02:14.715 --> 02:15.754
You are great.

02:15.755 --> 02:16.834
One of the greats, yes,

02:16.835 --> 02:18.504
but nobody's ever even heard of me.

02:18.505 --> 02:19.874
I know. It baffles me, too.

02:19.875 --> 02:21.914
I mean, you know how long
I've been tryin' to go up

02:21.915 --> 02:23.504
at The 8:30 Club, but just you watch.

02:23.505 --> 02:25.174
This campaign is gonna
change all of that.

02:25.175 --> 02:26.254
If you want to get discovered,

02:26.255 --> 02:27.414
just do it the old-fashioned way...

02:27.415 --> 02:28.674
by waiting for a nice old Jewish man

02:28.675 --> 02:29.754
to give you his business card.

02:29.755 --> 02:31.504
Or people see my name in the news,

02:31.505 --> 02:33.674
they look at my music,
the labels start circling.

02:33.675 --> 02:35.874
I'm like, "Guys, guys,
it's too much too fast."

02:35.875 --> 02:37.254
You know, just to be dramatic.

02:37.255 --> 02:38.964
And next thing you know,
me and Taylor Swift

02:38.965 --> 02:40.504
are doing a Super Bowl performance

02:40.505 --> 02:41.834
that red and blue states can enjoy.

02:41.835 --> 02:43.294
Lord, thank you for making him cute,

02:43.295 --> 02:44.794
because, otherwise,
we'd be in big trouble.

02:44.795 --> 02:46.464
Oh, tell him not to miss the debate.

02:46.465 --> 02:47.754
Wait, Ma, Ma, Ma, Ma, Ma. You know what?

02:47.755 --> 02:49.254
It's really dope that we're roommates.

02:49.255 --> 02:51.410
It's like we're fam
but also like we're fam.

02:51.435 --> 02:52.703
It's like you my mama,
but at the same time,

02:52.728 --> 02:54.001
- it's like you my ma. I love you!
- Mnh-mnh. Mnh-mnh.

02:54.061 --> 02:55.914
♪ Come and see me where I live, man ♪

02:55.915 --> 02:57.874
♪ Come and see me where I live, man ♪

02:57.875 --> 02:59.914
♪ Come and see me,
I'll be right here, Fort Grey ♪

02:59.915 --> 03:01.334
♪ Right here all day ♪

03:01.335 --> 03:02.335
♪ Right here in Northern California ♪

03:02.336 --> 03:04.255
- Boy: Go get it. Go get it, boy.
- [Dog barking]

03:04.280 --> 03:05.464
- ♪ Come and see me where I live, man ♪
- - Good boy.

03:05.465 --> 03:06.504
Courtney: What's up, little man?

03:06.505 --> 03:08.754
You, uh, protecting our city's...

03:08.755 --> 03:10.610
Aah! Yep, you probably shouldn't
touch stuff like that.

03:10.670 --> 03:12.214
Ernie wanted to play.

03:12.215 --> 03:14.914
He thinks it's a park because
he's a dog and dogs are dumb.

03:14.915 --> 03:16.294
Yo, you know, when I was your age,

03:16.295 --> 03:17.834
there wasn't all this trash here.

03:17.835 --> 03:20.044
Me and my boys, we would
come here to freestyle.

03:20.045 --> 03:22.464
And there was this rapper, Mac Etcetera,

03:22.465 --> 03:23.624
we always wanted to be.

03:23.625 --> 03:24.794
You're a rapper?

03:24.795 --> 03:26.851
Like Eminem, Macklemore,

03:26.875 --> 03:27.813
- and Iggy Azalea?
- Hmm.

03:27.838 --> 03:29.334
Yeah, yeah, yeah,
that list is hella problematic,

03:29.335 --> 03:31.544
but, yes, I am a rapper.

03:31.545 --> 03:33.084
All right, man. Get home safe.

03:33.085 --> 03:34.464
All right.

03:34.465 --> 03:36.714
♪ Same house, same bike,
same crew, same gripe ♪

03:36.715 --> 03:38.414
♪ Man, only thing changed is the shoes ♪

03:38.415 --> 03:40.584
- T.K.! Jermaine!
- Ah!

03:40.585 --> 03:43.084
Here we are. It's the big debate.

03:43.085 --> 03:45.714
After this, I will be blowin' up
on the charts.

03:45.715 --> 03:47.754
I wonder if I should cut off
my non-famous friends.

03:47.755 --> 03:49.294
I mean, like, I-I'll miss 'em,

03:49.295 --> 03:51.544
but it's like what do we
even talk about, you know?

03:51.545 --> 03:52.875
- Okay.
- I've already done the mic check.

03:52.876 --> 03:54.294
They tried telling me it was too loud,

03:54.295 --> 03:55.334
but I told 'em, "Trust me."

03:55.335 --> 03:57.214
They were right. It was too loud.

03:57.215 --> 03:59.414
- It was too loud.
- Oh, Valentine Barella!

03:59.415 --> 04:02.414
My 10th-grade lab partner,
now my political adversary.

04:02.415 --> 04:04.174
So what's the messaging tonight, huh?

04:04.175 --> 04:06.414
[Rapping] ♪ My name is
Courtney, and I'm here to say ♪

04:06.415 --> 04:07.834
- That's not bad.
- Don't worry.

04:07.835 --> 04:09.794
You have nothing to lose tonight
except your street cred,

04:09.795 --> 04:11.414
your dignity, and your self-respect.

04:11.415 --> 04:13.084
Small stuff. Good luck.

04:13.085 --> 04:16.374
- Ouch!
- That hurt my feelings.

04:16.375 --> 04:18.004
Aaron: The Honorable Ellen Trout,

04:18.005 --> 04:22.124
Councilman Ed Gunt,
and Courtney Rose... rapper.

04:22.125 --> 04:23.544
- [Whistling]
- Whoo-whoo-whoo!

04:23.545 --> 04:24.874
- Courtney!
- I'm a nervous wreck.

04:24.875 --> 04:27.334
He didn't prep. He refused
to put on foundation.

04:27.335 --> 04:28.255
Why do you have makeup?

04:28.256 --> 04:30.414
What? Wow. Wow.

04:30.415 --> 04:32.004
That's a little queerphobic, but okay.

04:32.005 --> 04:33.214
You're not queer.

04:33.215 --> 04:35.624
With intolerance like that
in the world, thank God.

04:35.625 --> 04:36.965
- You know what?
- Nope. You said it.

04:36.968 --> 04:39.754
Mr. Rose, as mayor, would you uphold

04:39.755 --> 04:43.334
or overturn the Grover-Stevens
bill to expand school choice?

04:43.335 --> 04:45.044
Uh, Grover-Stevens?

04:45.045 --> 04:46.504
Uh, sure. Yeah, yeah, yeah.

04:46.505 --> 04:48.464
I-I happen to be tight
with Grover-Stevens.

04:48.465 --> 04:51.004
- [Chuckles]
- Grover and Stevens, big guy.

04:51.005 --> 04:52.045
- It's two people.
- [Laughter]

04:52.048 --> 04:54.914
But is... is this bill good,
or is it bad?

04:54.915 --> 04:56.794
I mean, who are we, really, to judge?

04:56.795 --> 04:58.794
Because at the end of the day,

04:58.795 --> 05:00.794
there's only one judge that matters...

05:00.819 --> 05:02.320
a young carpenter.

05:02.345 --> 05:03.235
[Chuckles]

05:03.236 --> 05:04.294
[Laughter]

05:04.295 --> 05:06.504
Okay. You know what this is.

05:06.505 --> 05:09.174
Don't fall for it.
This is a funny distraction.

05:09.175 --> 05:11.964
It's cute. I like it. I like you.

05:11.965 --> 05:16.624
So let's laugh at this and get
back to work fixing our city.

05:16.625 --> 05:19.214
[Applause]

05:19.215 --> 05:21.084
As you know, Drea,

05:21.085 --> 05:25.504
I am the proud son of
a steelworker and her husband.

05:25.505 --> 05:26.965
- [Chuckles] Yes.
- [Audience "awws"]

05:26.968 --> 05:28.504
My folks weren't rich,

05:28.505 --> 05:31.124
but what they lacked in wealth
they made up for with love.

05:31.125 --> 05:33.045
- [Audience "awws"]
- Point being,

05:33.046 --> 05:35.294
I'm proud to have led the effort
to restore the City Commons,

05:35.295 --> 05:36.675
- which is now well under way.
- Whoa.

05:36.678 --> 05:39.084
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Hold up.

05:39.085 --> 05:42.544
Um, it's not every day that
you [Chuckles] hear "proud"

05:42.545 --> 05:44.930
and "City Commons"
used in the same sentence.

05:44.955 --> 05:46.044
I mean, I was just there.

05:46.045 --> 05:48.174
Have you actually ever
been there, Mr. Gunt?

05:48.175 --> 05:50.175
- I know these people have.
- [Cheers and applause]

05:50.176 --> 05:52.754
[Chuckles] I mean,
there is so much trash,

05:52.755 --> 05:55.300
Google Maps has it listed as a mountain.

05:55.325 --> 05:56.625
- [Laughter]
- You know what I'm saying?

05:56.628 --> 05:58.214
Like, a saw a rat riding a toboggan

05:58.215 --> 05:59.964
down one of them things the other day.

05:59.965 --> 06:02.714
It's so much trash,
Bravo gave it a second season.

06:02.715 --> 06:04.214
[Laughter, applause]

06:04.215 --> 06:07.906
Which is why I pledge that, by 2020,

06:07.931 --> 06:10.726
all that trash will be gone.

06:10.751 --> 06:12.124
And by "gone,"

06:12.125 --> 06:15.834
he means underneath the new
trash from 2018 and 2019.

06:15.835 --> 06:18.874
I mean, come on, help me out here, fam.

06:18.875 --> 06:21.174
I mean, how many of y'all
drove here today

06:21.175 --> 06:23.464
in a busted-up car from all
of our busted-up streets?

06:23.465 --> 06:25.124
And who's going home tonight

06:25.125 --> 06:27.044
to a building with boarded-up windows?

06:27.045 --> 06:28.636
I mean, hey, it beats

06:28.661 --> 06:30.856
looking at all that gang
graffiti, though, right?

06:30.881 --> 06:32.044
[Cheers and applause]

06:32.045 --> 06:36.334
I mean, don't... don't tell us
about our reality, Mr. Gunt.

06:36.335 --> 06:38.754
Because we live our reality every day.

06:38.755 --> 06:40.674
I hate to interrupt
the dog-and-pony show,

06:40.675 --> 06:43.624
but urban development, it takes time.
You wouldn't know that.

06:43.625 --> 06:45.006
What are you doing?

06:45.031 --> 06:46.673
Oh, I'm just calling [bleep].

06:46.698 --> 06:49.124
- Okay.
- Mr. Rose.

06:49.125 --> 06:52.374
Mr. Rose, now seems like a
fitting time for this question.

06:52.375 --> 06:54.914
Are you running for mayor of Fort Grey,

06:54.915 --> 06:57.600
or are you promoting a rap album?

06:57.625 --> 07:00.914
Wow. Wow, I have to say that I am hurt

07:00.915 --> 07:04.593
that you think that I would be
here to sell some silly album

07:04.618 --> 07:06.860
that's already available on my website

07:06.885 --> 07:10.124
at www.MusicByCourtney.com.

07:10.125 --> 07:14.834
Can we stop this?
Can a grown-up please intervene?

07:14.835 --> 07:19.687
These lovely voters have been asking
that same question for 25 years.

07:19.712 --> 07:21.051
Pow, pow!

07:21.052 --> 07:22.751
You know what?

07:22.752 --> 07:24.841
You folks have been great.

07:24.842 --> 07:27.251
I'm Courtney Rose! Out! Peace!

07:27.252 --> 07:28.132
[Theme music plays]

07:28.133 --> 07:29.591
Welcome back to Channel 8's

07:29.592 --> 07:31.461
around-the-clock election coverage.

07:31.462 --> 07:33.921
This is incredible.

07:33.922 --> 07:35.671
Ever since the debate last week,

07:35.672 --> 07:37.511
my mix tape is getting some crazy love.

07:37.512 --> 07:38.961
Guess how many total downloads.

07:38.962 --> 07:40.751
Conservative? 20 million.

07:40.752 --> 07:42.503
20 million? Brah, that would put me

07:42.528 --> 07:44.051
in between The Beatles and Rihanna.

07:44.052 --> 07:45.801
Forgive me for believing in you,
Courtney.

07:45.802 --> 07:47.549
<i>And, Beau, it looks like we'll be able</i>

07:47.573 --> 07:49.214
- <i>to do that right away.</i>
- What's happening?

07:49.215 --> 07:51.672
- Mom, we all out of the good soap?
- <i>...our friends from Fort Grey Free Press</i>

07:51.673 --> 07:53.212
- <i>have the election calculations for us.</i>
- The antibacterial?

07:53.215 --> 07:54.801
Why isn't every soap antibacterial?

07:54.802 --> 07:55.851
- <i>And I certainly cannot.</i>
- Shh!

07:55.852 --> 07:59.437
<i>It appears as if local rapper
Courtney Rose</i>

07:59.462 --> 08:02.011
<i>is our projected winner
in the race for mayor</i>

08:02.012 --> 08:03.252
- <i>of Fort Grey, California.</i>
- [Toilet flushes]

08:03.277 --> 08:05.317
- Oh!
- <i>Wow!</i>

08:05.342 --> 08:07.131
What? What happened?

08:07.132 --> 08:08.381
<i>Wow.</i>

08:08.382 --> 08:09.711
What happened is...

08:09.712 --> 08:10.961
you the mayor.

08:10.962 --> 08:14.341
♪♪

08:14.342 --> 08:16.052
Well [bleep].

08:17.519 --> 08:19.374
- Hey, this has to be a mistake.
- [Telephone ringing]

08:19.399 --> 08:22.280
I mean, Russia clearly tampered
with the voting machines, right?

08:22.305 --> 08:24.766
I don't think it's a mistake, man.
I mean, the media is never wrong.

08:24.813 --> 08:25.966
- So what do I do?
- [Cellphones ringing]

08:26.033 --> 08:28.602
I mean, how do you go about
not being the mayor?

08:28.603 --> 08:30.272
Well, the first step would probably be

08:30.273 --> 08:31.482
not running for mayor.

08:31.483 --> 08:33.152
- Okay, you want my two cents?
- [Groans]

08:33.153 --> 08:34.692
Uh, listen. Hear me out, okay?

08:34.693 --> 08:36.232
I say you serve for one day only.

08:36.232 --> 08:37.892
That way, you can get the scissors.

08:37.893 --> 08:40.152
- The scissors?
- The scissors.

08:40.153 --> 08:42.732
The... The... The giant scissors
they give mayors to cut ribbons.

08:42.732 --> 08:44.732
It's politics 101, man.
Come on, stop playin'.

08:44.733 --> 08:48.392
Oh, yeah, I-I'm gonna go down
to City Hall and tell the clerk,

08:48.393 --> 08:51.062
"Hard pass, but I'm still
putting this on my résumé."

08:51.063 --> 08:52.652
- Oh, no. No, you...
- No! Go get the scissors.

08:52.653 --> 08:55.062
- Yes, I am, because...
- Fire!

08:55.063 --> 08:56.063
Oh, oh, oh!

08:56.064 --> 08:57.522
[Sour notes play]

08:57.523 --> 08:58.772
Wh-Where is it?!

08:58.773 --> 09:00.062
It just means that we're going out

09:00.063 --> 09:01.232
to the fire escape to have a talk.

09:01.233 --> 09:02.812
I can see how it can be
a little confusing.

09:02.837 --> 09:04.286
Ms. Dina, you can't yell "fire"

09:04.311 --> 09:05.853
- at black people like that.
- That's all you had to say.

09:05.853 --> 09:07.272
- I'm skittish. I get to...
- You got to leave it.

09:07.273 --> 09:10.892
I've given you a lot of
straight talk on this, uh...

09:10.893 --> 09:13.022
oh, let's just call it a balcony.

09:13.023 --> 09:15.692
"The fountain at the mall
is not a pool, Courtney.

09:15.693 --> 09:17.892
No, you will not be
piercing that, Courtney."

09:17.893 --> 09:21.232
[Sighs] Courtney, listen to me.

09:21.233 --> 09:24.312
You put your name on a ballot.

09:24.313 --> 09:26.442
In this country, that means something.

09:26.443 --> 09:27.982
It carries consequences.

09:27.983 --> 09:29.812
It's you telling the people,

09:29.813 --> 09:31.772
"I want to make your life better."

09:31.773 --> 09:34.892
And tonight, the people said, "Okay."

09:34.893 --> 09:36.772
Yeah, but they couldn't
just buy my ringtone?

09:36.773 --> 09:39.392
[Sighs] Tell me something.
Why do you rap?

09:39.393 --> 09:41.192
That cash-money lifestyle, obviously.

09:41.193 --> 09:42.522
Do not be cute.

09:42.523 --> 09:45.352
You rap because you're...
you're a commentator.

09:45.353 --> 09:46.732
You're an observer.

09:46.733 --> 09:49.482
You critique the status quo.

09:49.483 --> 09:52.692
Baby, maybe now you can
actually change it.

09:52.693 --> 09:54.482
Wow.

09:54.483 --> 09:57.152
Ma, I have to say,
that was hella poignant.

09:57.153 --> 10:00.392
[Dog barking in distance]

10:00.393 --> 10:03.772
You know what, Ma?

10:03.773 --> 10:05.312
I think I got this.

10:05.313 --> 10:06.352
- Damn right you do.
- Yeah.

10:06.353 --> 10:09.312
Who my baby? My baby the mayor!

10:09.313 --> 10:10.602
[Clears throat]

10:10.603 --> 10:12.522
[Gasps] Whoa! Whoa!

10:12.523 --> 10:13.772
What are you...

10:13.773 --> 10:15.772
I'm sorry. Did I invade your privacy?

10:15.773 --> 10:17.852
Get used to it.
You're a public figure now.

10:17.853 --> 10:19.192
Cream with three sugars.

10:19.193 --> 10:21.602
Are you here to, like, assassinate me?

10:21.603 --> 10:23.852
[Chuckles] Well, we'll see
how the conversation goes.

10:23.853 --> 10:26.272
Courtney... [Sighs]
I want to run your staff.

10:26.273 --> 10:29.732
If I can turn all of this into
a halfway functioning mayor,

10:29.733 --> 10:31.652
well, then I will just join the pantheon

10:31.653 --> 10:33.062
of female political masterminds,

10:33.063 --> 10:34.732
just crushing every Kellyanne Conway

10:34.733 --> 10:36.102
and Donna Brazile in my path.

10:36.103 --> 10:38.652
I'm very intimidated
by other women's success.

10:38.653 --> 10:40.352
That was a joke.

10:40.353 --> 10:41.603
Hilarious. Relevant.

10:41.683 --> 10:44.732
Courtney, listen, do yourself a favor.
Let me help you.

10:44.733 --> 10:46.812
I know it needs to get done,
and I know how to do it.

10:46.813 --> 10:48.982
Wow. You do bring a lot to the table.

10:48.983 --> 10:51.732
Three citywide campaigns,
two years with the Comptroller,

10:51.733 --> 10:53.522
and what does that all add up to?

10:53.523 --> 10:55.102
A very unsexy LinkedIn page.

10:55.127 --> 10:56.106
Like, seriously, you got to zazz

10:56.130 --> 10:57.154
- this up or something.
- Okay.

10:57.179 --> 10:58.392
I'm gonna need to know
that you're committed,

10:58.393 --> 11:00.272
'cause I don't work seven days
a week for someone who's not.

11:00.273 --> 11:02.102
Well, to show how committed I am,

11:02.103 --> 11:04.602
I am going to clear
my entire touring schedule.

11:04.603 --> 11:06.594
I doubt you have a touring
schedule, but we'll go with it.

11:06.619 --> 11:07.562
[Sighs]

11:07.563 --> 11:09.272
So it's a deal.

11:09.273 --> 11:11.022
Mm.

11:11.023 --> 11:12.392
Great, and, look, Courtney,

11:12.393 --> 11:14.352
I've been around a lot of politicians,

11:14.353 --> 11:16.982
and... you have something special.

11:16.983 --> 11:18.948
- Yeah, what's that?
- Me.

11:18.973 --> 11:21.019
<i>♪ It's in the... ♪</i>

11:21.193 --> 11:23.711
<i>- ♪ Let's go to work ♪
- ♪ Yeah, go to work ♪</i>

11:23.736 --> 11:26.258
<i>♪ Yeah, go to work ♪</i>

11:26.283 --> 11:27.272
<i>♪ Yeah ♪</i>

11:27.273 --> 11:28.852
- <i>♪ Go to work ♪</i>
- [Camera shutter clicks]

11:28.853 --> 11:32.022
I found you the absolute best
staffers in the county...

11:32.023 --> 11:33.606
but they weren't available.

11:34.393 --> 11:36.594
Hi. I'm Kitty Kavanagh.

11:36.619 --> 11:37.982
I'm handling your press.

11:37.983 --> 11:40.353
- I'm very excited to learn your voice.
- Oh, boy.

11:40.356 --> 11:42.772
- Dick Papadopolous, DMV guy.
- Hi.

11:42.773 --> 11:45.652
We let people self-report
their weight on licenses,

11:45.653 --> 11:47.692
so I'm okay bending the truth.

11:47.693 --> 11:50.383
- [Clears throat] Okay.
- Thank you for that.

11:50.407 --> 11:51.584
I'll remember that. It's disturbing.

11:51.609 --> 11:52.892
Okay, we will get started.

11:52.893 --> 11:53.893
- Sorry we're late.
- What's up?

11:53.894 --> 11:55.652
- Hey!
- We had to buy notebooks.

11:55.653 --> 11:57.812
Uh, I'm assuming we bill this
to the city?

11:57.813 --> 11:59.229
I'll start a file.

11:59.276 --> 12:00.575
- What's going on?
- Huh? Oh.

12:00.576 --> 12:01.663
I hired a few staffers.

12:01.688 --> 12:03.983
These boys know Fort Grey
inside and out.

12:03.996 --> 12:06.084
And if I needed a pizza
delivered in 60 minutes or less,

12:06.109 --> 12:07.677
- they would be my guys.
- I can do it in 12.

12:07.702 --> 12:10.075
Doesn't matter. All right, so,
we start the transition

12:10.076 --> 12:11.875
with figuring out the first 100 days.

12:11.876 --> 12:14.335
What I like to do is use index cards

12:14.336 --> 12:16.575
to organize the important issues.

12:16.576 --> 12:18.495
So, as you can see,

12:18.496 --> 12:20.995
green index cards are for
fiscal issues, obviously.

12:20.996 --> 12:23.375
Blue index cards are for social issues.

12:23.376 --> 12:25.786
- Red index cards are for...
- Oh, if I hear "index cards" one more time,

12:25.787 --> 12:27.035
- I'm going out the window.
- Mm-hmm.

12:27.036 --> 12:29.035
No revolution in history
has ever started

12:29.036 --> 12:31.067
- with the words "index cards."
- Preach, Courtney.

12:31.092 --> 12:32.915
Why did 52% of the city vote for me?

12:32.916 --> 12:34.335
Because they are sick and tired

12:34.336 --> 12:36.375
of hearing what phonies intend to do.

12:36.376 --> 12:38.335
What did you have in mind,
she asked with a tone.

12:38.336 --> 12:40.205
- The City Commons.
- Mm-hmm.

12:40.206 --> 12:42.075
People really feel connected
to the place.

12:42.076 --> 12:44.955
They remember hanging out there
back in the day like we used to.

12:44.956 --> 12:46.745
I say we transform

12:46.746 --> 12:47.995
- that hideous dump...
- Yes.

12:47.996 --> 12:50.125
Into the most beautiful dump
you have ever seen.

12:50.126 --> 12:51.665
And the best part about it...

12:51.666 --> 12:53.785
We can do it right now
without spending a dime.

12:53.786 --> 12:54.666
- Now, wait a minute.
- Uh-huh.

12:54.667 --> 12:55.835
- Did you say right now...
- Uh-huh.

12:55.836 --> 12:56.706
- ...without spending a dime?
- Yes, I did.

12:56.707 --> 12:58.915
- But how?
- By doing what we do,

12:58.916 --> 13:00.785
throwing the party of the millennium!

13:00.786 --> 13:02.915
Beer, barbecue, brooms, buckets!

13:02.916 --> 13:04.495
- Turn up and clean up.
- Boom.

13:04.496 --> 13:07.875
Okay, Courtney, I love a party
just as much as the next guy,

13:07.876 --> 13:09.285
but there's a process.

13:09.286 --> 13:10.916
- You need a permit. You need the...
- So we'll get a permit.

13:10.919 --> 13:12.575
And we can round up people in hours.

13:12.576 --> 13:13.955
I mean, Jermaine, how long did it take

13:13.956 --> 13:15.625
to gather people for my "Red Sky" video?

13:15.626 --> 13:17.254
- Less than a month.
- Took us a day.

13:17.279 --> 13:18.794
Well, we had to wait
for Wild Man to get here.

13:18.819 --> 13:19.705
Oh, you remember Wild Man?

13:19.706 --> 13:20.706
- Right.
- Okay, Wild Man. Okay.

13:20.706 --> 13:21.706
- Look, trust me.
- Forgot about him.

13:21.707 --> 13:23.875
- Once we pull this off,
- Wild man.

13:23.876 --> 13:26.455
the voters will only have
one question...

13:26.456 --> 13:28.075
"Why'd it take 25 years?"

13:28.076 --> 13:29.835
- Oh. Wow.
- Come on. Did y'all feel that?

13:29.836 --> 13:31.745
- Did y'all feel that?
- Write a book.

