13:52.126 --> 13:53.625
<i>♪ When yuh ah guh learn, learn,
learn, learn, learn, learn ♪</i>

13:53.626 --> 13:56.336
What's up, Fort Grey, Californ-i-a?!

13:56.409 --> 13:57.575
[Cheers and applause]

13:57.576 --> 14:00.285
I just want to thank you all for
proving my long-held conviction

14:00.286 --> 14:03.705
that anything is possible if you
load people up on cheap beer.

14:03.706 --> 14:04.666
- Yes.
- [Laughter]

14:04.669 --> 14:05.705
Courtney.

14:05.730 --> 14:08.382
But, seriously, after this,
if you all could please

14:08.436 --> 14:09.344
- come back to my apartment.
- Okay, maybe go up there.

14:09.369 --> 14:10.995
- Yeah. Okay, okay.
- My closet is a disaster.

14:10.996 --> 14:12.705
Okay, baby, give me the thing.

14:12.706 --> 14:15.165
Hey! Is he a bundle from heaven or what?

14:15.166 --> 14:17.304
Thank you for helping us
at City Commons,

14:17.329 --> 14:18.464
but there's still work to do,

14:18.489 --> 14:20.391
so I need you to pick up trash
and not just get trashed, huh?

14:20.416 --> 14:22.125
- Mr. Mayor-elect?
- All right!

14:22.126 --> 14:24.835
I'm afraid to even ask, but you
did remember the permit, right?

14:24.836 --> 14:26.336
Classic.

14:26.396 --> 14:27.565
Oh, sh...

14:27.566 --> 14:28.935
Great.

14:28.936 --> 14:30.975
Oh, I knew I forgot something,

14:30.976 --> 14:32.396
- and that something...
- Mm-hmm.

14:32.399 --> 14:36.065
...is my permit-having victory dance!

14:36.066 --> 14:37.066
Like, what?

14:37.067 --> 14:38.265
Okay. All right.

14:38.266 --> 14:39.396
[Laughs] Love it.

14:39.397 --> 14:40.525
I'm almost impressed.

14:40.526 --> 14:42.265
I could bust the worm
if I had more space.

14:42.266 --> 14:43.816
- I could do backflips.
- [Laughs]

14:43.819 --> 14:45.645
- Yo, man, I feel so fulfilled.
- Yeah.

14:45.646 --> 14:47.629
- It's kind of like we're both the mayor,
- [Cellphone ringing]

14:47.654 --> 14:49.605
- you know?
- Hello.

14:49.606 --> 14:52.525
Yeah, man. Um...

14:52.526 --> 14:53.855
Like, for real?

14:53.856 --> 14:55.895
No, no. No, no, no, no.

14:55.896 --> 14:58.645
Um, uh, let... let me...
let me call you right back.

14:58.646 --> 15:01.646
- Wrong number?
- That was the booker from The 8:30 Club.

15:01.649 --> 15:03.025
Their opener canceled,
and they thought about,

15:03.026 --> 15:04.605
"How about the mayor kid?"

15:04.606 --> 15:06.065
Brah, guess who's headlining.

15:06.066 --> 15:07.605
- Who?
- Mac Etcetera.

15:07.606 --> 15:09.568
Ah!

15:09.593 --> 15:12.935
- When is it?!
- Uh, it's happening in about...

15:12.936 --> 15:14.395
eight minutes.

15:14.396 --> 15:15.765
I would be insane not to go, right?

15:15.766 --> 15:17.525
I mean, the second hand
is moving crazy fast.

15:17.526 --> 15:20.315
No, no, no, Courtney, look, if I
was you, here's what I would do.

15:20.316 --> 15:23.935
I would ask me, and I, you,
would tell you, me, don't go.

15:23.936 --> 15:24.975
Oh, so you're conflicted, too.

15:24.976 --> 15:27.265
Courtney, l-look.
Look at this party, man.

15:27.266 --> 15:28.855
There's still work to do, man,

15:28.880 --> 15:32.145
and you made a commitment
to all these people.

15:32.186 --> 15:33.688
Courtney!

15:34.482 --> 15:36.722
♪ Who the greatest player walkin',
but they tell you I'm the champ ♪

15:36.795 --> 15:38.663
- ♪ Better catch me if you can ♪
- Come on, come on.

15:38.688 --> 15:39.758
♪ You gonna miss me when I'm gone, son ♪

15:39.783 --> 15:40.795
♪ Where the Mac gonna go next,
I don't know ♪

15:40.820 --> 15:42.622
♪ But you can bet I'm gonna be on one ♪

15:42.623 --> 15:44.083
- [Indistinct conversations]
- Hey,

15:44.086 --> 15:47.910
- have you seen Courtney?
- Uh... i-is that him, blue stripes?

15:48.017 --> 15:49.235
The white guy?

15:49.297 --> 15:52.006
Yeah, that... that ain't him.

15:52.558 --> 15:55.256
- Has anyone seen Courtney?
- Fort Grey.

15:55.257 --> 15:56.716
I want y'all to make some noise

15:56.717 --> 15:59.500
for the next mayor of Fort Grey,
California, Courtney Rose.

15:59.525 --> 16:01.466
[Cheers and applause]

16:01.467 --> 16:05.046
♪♪

16:05.047 --> 16:07.336
[Siren wailing, tire screetches]

16:07.337 --> 16:10.006
♪♪

16:10.737 --> 16:12.838
- Officer. Hi.
- Mm-hmm. Yeah.

16:12.863 --> 16:14.196
E-Everything all right?

16:14.197 --> 16:16.510
We've received several noise complaints,

16:16.535 --> 16:19.196
and I'm gonna need to see
a public-assembly permit.

16:19.197 --> 16:21.616
You are in luck because
we have one of those.

16:21.617 --> 16:22.656
Where's Courtney?

16:22.657 --> 16:24.736
That is something I'm also wondering

16:24.737 --> 16:27.696
because I don't know where Courtney is.

16:27.697 --> 16:29.406
[Indistinct conversations]

16:29.407 --> 16:30.906
Okay.

16:30.907 --> 16:33.656
♪ But I came up just in Drake's club ♪

16:33.657 --> 16:36.206
- ♪ When you get up, don't step back ♪
- Hey!

16:36.260 --> 16:38.466
Officer, why don't you
give me your phone number,

16:38.467 --> 16:39.796
and maybe I can just text you

16:39.797 --> 16:41.506
a picture of the permit later tonight?

16:41.507 --> 16:43.546
That didn't sound like
a solicitation, did it?

16:43.547 --> 16:45.296
I'm not giving you my phone number.

16:45.297 --> 16:47.716
Officer: Party's over, folks.
Vacate the premises.

16:47.717 --> 16:49.177
- [Crowd booing]
- Go home.

16:49.178 --> 16:50.876
- All right, let's go.
- Oh! Don't touch me!

16:50.877 --> 16:52.216
Dina: I am a mail woman.

16:52.217 --> 16:54.136
Do you want your Christmas cards
showing up in March?

16:54.137 --> 16:57.796
If I have to say it again,
citations will be issued.

16:57.797 --> 16:59.466
Citations? Oh, I'll take a citation

16:59.467 --> 17:00.966
if you can tell me one person up in here

17:00.967 --> 17:01.967
that knows what a citation is.

17:01.967 --> 17:02.967
- You don't even know what a...
- Dina.

17:02.968 --> 17:04.715
I got this... what a citation is.

17:04.717 --> 17:06.006
I know what an arrest is.

17:06.007 --> 17:08.337
Arrest? I'd like to see you try.

17:10.257 --> 17:13.256
The prison industrial complex.

17:13.257 --> 17:15.215
If I come out of here a killer,
that's on you.

17:15.217 --> 17:17.136
Thank you all so much right now!

17:17.137 --> 17:18.586
Thank you to Mac Etcetera!

17:18.587 --> 17:21.046
You just made a childhood dream
come true.

17:21.047 --> 17:23.465
I just hope the clink
didn't break your spirit.

17:23.467 --> 17:25.175
I'm here, I'm here!

17:25.176 --> 17:27.006
I got your message, Ma.

17:27.007 --> 17:28.926
Guys, look, can I...

17:28.927 --> 17:30.176
- can I just say real quick...
- Dina: You know what you can say?

17:30.177 --> 17:32.676
You can say nothing.
That's what you can say.

17:32.677 --> 17:35.756
You basically handcuffed
and arrested your own mother.

17:35.757 --> 17:36.966
Our mother.

17:36.967 --> 17:38.676
And you wonder why
she likes me more than you.

17:38.677 --> 17:40.466
- No, T.K.
- Well, agree to disagree.

17:40.467 --> 17:42.676
Look, we put our reputations
on the line for you, Courtney,

17:42.677 --> 17:44.426
a-and I barely have one as it is.

17:44.427 --> 17:46.336
You know what? I'm out. I'm done.

17:46.337 --> 17:47.427
Goodbye.

17:49.587 --> 17:51.216
- I don't have a ride.
- Mm-hmm.

17:51.217 --> 17:52.796
Dina: Fool, come on.

17:52.797 --> 17:54.466
You know, Courtney? [Sighs]

17:54.467 --> 17:57.256
I feel bad for the 52% of
the people who voted for you

17:57.257 --> 17:59.546
because you just made a fool
out of all of them.

17:59.547 --> 18:01.006
Hopeless.

18:01.007 --> 18:03.586
♪♪

18:03.587 --> 18:06.546
Courtney: I'm sorry, Ma.
I am so embarrassed.

18:06.547 --> 18:08.876
Courtney, I am your mother.

18:08.877 --> 18:12.506
I have been your mother
since I was 16 years old.

18:12.507 --> 18:15.426
And no matter what penitentiary
you send me to,

18:15.427 --> 18:17.876
you are my son, and I'll believe in you.

18:17.877 --> 18:19.796
But, unfortunately,

18:19.797 --> 18:21.926
everyone else in the world
ain't your mama.

18:21.927 --> 18:24.426
I know. I-I wish they had
locked me up instead of you.

18:24.427 --> 18:25.466
Okay, well, first choice,

18:25.467 --> 18:26.586
neither one of us being locked up.

18:26.587 --> 18:28.466
Courtney, listen.

18:28.467 --> 18:31.466
This is not about you anymore.

18:31.467 --> 18:36.756
Your actions have consequences
for a lot of people, our people.

18:36.757 --> 18:41.676
Your failures are their failures.

18:41.677 --> 18:44.508
Okay. I know what I have to do.

18:44.533 --> 18:47.466
Okay.

18:47.467 --> 18:49.705
Do you want to say it first,
or you want me to say it

18:49.730 --> 18:51.113
- just to make sure we're on the same page?
- Are you kidding me right now?!

18:51.138 --> 18:52.676
Okay, we'll... we'll
compare notes later.

18:52.677 --> 18:53.926
That's fine.

18:53.927 --> 18:55.837
- [Keys jingle]
- [Engine starts]

18:55.840 --> 18:57.587
- [Cellphone rings]
- <i>Hi. You've reached Courtney Rose.</i>

18:57.590 --> 19:00.006
<i>♪ ThePeoplesCourtney.
[Laughs] Leave a message.</i>

19:00.007 --> 19:01.796
Voicemail. Where's Courtney?

19:01.797 --> 19:03.716
What? What, guys?

19:03.717 --> 19:05.876
What's so important that you
couldn't tell me over the phone?

19:05.877 --> 19:09.466
- Um...
- Courtney is no longer with us.

19:09.467 --> 19:12.006
Okay, that was a weird way
to phrase that.

19:12.007 --> 19:13.926
I mean we can't find him.

19:13.927 --> 19:16.256
Indifference with subtle notes
of disdain.

19:16.257 --> 19:17.296
Yeah, I see that.

19:17.297 --> 19:19.006
I'm not joining your search party,

19:19.007 --> 19:20.836
and this isn't one of those situations

19:20.837 --> 19:23.157
where I say one thing
and then I eventually cave.

19:24.257 --> 19:25.427
I'm serious.

19:26.797 --> 19:27.967
Stop looking at me.

19:29.927 --> 19:31.370
Okay, let's go find him.

19:31.430 --> 19:32.426
- All right.
- Thank you.

19:32.427 --> 19:34.506
- Val, we checked everywhere.
- Did you check the commons?

19:34.507 --> 19:35.867
Okay, we did not check everywhere.

19:37.797 --> 19:38.942
It all looks amazing.

19:38.943 --> 19:40.086
- Oh, my God.
- Wow.

19:40.087 --> 19:41.506
Look at this place.

19:41.507 --> 19:42.836
There's my man!

19:42.837 --> 19:44.136
I can't believe he finished this.

19:44.137 --> 19:46.411
Man, this is the most beautiful
dump I have ever seen.

19:46.436 --> 19:47.756
Hey, guys.

19:47.757 --> 19:49.796
I figured I had
some unfinished business,

19:49.797 --> 19:52.586
so I, uh, put in a couple extra hours.

19:52.587 --> 19:55.334
We were just worried about you,
man, and... and angry with you.

19:55.359 --> 19:56.608
It was very complicated.

19:56.633 --> 19:58.682
- I mean, this rich emotional stew.
- Yeah.

19:58.707 --> 20:00.323
Courtney: Sorry. I'm sorry, guys.

20:00.324 --> 20:02.953
I turned my phone off
so I could avoid distractions.

20:02.954 --> 20:04.613
Oh, I could never turn off my phone.

20:04.614 --> 20:06.534
- What?
- What? I-I get Internet on this thing.

20:06.537 --> 20:08.243
I ain't never had an Internet phone.

20:08.244 --> 20:10.203
You know, you didn't have to do
all this by yourself, Courtney.

20:10.204 --> 20:11.913
You could've called me.
I mean, I had stuff.

20:11.914 --> 20:13.310
And I wouldn't have been there,
